\ELANParticipant segmentheader

\dt 07/Mar/2005                     
\cm beginning of second segment, originally
SukuFoun2_wmmb_vdp_29MAR03_01

TranskripsiMB

2 sampai 485 sebagian besar Tetun = this segment almost entirely consists of Tetum utterances, with some waima'a phrases interspersed. In this it is quite representative of the political speaking style of people native of Caisido, but living in Dili or Baucau with jobs in government or bigger businesses.

Towards the end, there is a longer stretch of Waima'a speech.

